"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armand_Duplantis\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Armand_Duplantis\"}, {\"begin\": 471, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"score\": 0.9999757607256562, \"rank\": 1.3090048962829977e-05, \"text\": \"Sweden\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sweden\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Will the women's final come with such an emotional bonus?\", \"from\": 570, \"to\": 627, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We will find out Wednesday.\", \"from\": 628, \"to\": 655, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Will the men's discus be as historic as Team USA's Valarie Allman becoming the second woman in history to win back-to-back discus titles?\", \"from\": 657, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 697, \"end\": 705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.999997126369444, \"rank\": 2.662647763872102e-06, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 708, \"end\": 722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valarie_Allman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Valarie Allman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valarie_Allman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Valarie_Allman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We will find out Wednesday.\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 822, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The track and field competition began Aug. 1 and will end Aug. 11.The first half already has provided some unforgettable moments.\", \"from\": 824, \"to\": 953, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's 400-meter event also will be concluding during Wednesday's coverage from Stade de France in Paris, and that's sure to keep viewers on the edges of their seats for another breathtaking 45 seconds.\", \"from\": 955, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1038, \"end\": 1053, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1057, \"end\": 1062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999961346, \"rank\": 3.8380727115385075e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Add in the semifinals of the men's 110-meter hurdles, men's 400-meter hurdles, men's 200-meter dash and the women's 400, plus the final of the men's 3,000-meter steeplechase, and there will not be a dull moment - whether you are up late to catch the beginning of the action or spending your afternoon glued to the TV - or both.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's the schedule for Day 7 of the track and field competition at the 2024 Summer Olympics:  All Times Eastern  The final of the men's pole vault at the 2024 Summer Olympics in Paris was filled with history and emotion.\", \"from\": 1491, \"to\": 1712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1670, \"end\": 1675, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999961346, \"rank\": 3.8380727115385075e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Simply enough, the men set the bar pretty high for the women, who will compete for their medals Wednesday at 1 p.m. Eastern.\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Everyone's talking about the men's pole vault final last night.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 1903, \"entities\